    name: "Epigenetic changes",
    body: "Epigenetics involves changes in the way genes are expressed without changing the DNA itself. Age-related epigenetic changes can activate \"bad\" genes and turn off \"good\" ones, leading to aging. Exercise, a clean diet, caloric restriction and supplements like resveratrol (found in grapes and red wine) can help maintain youthful gene expression, keeping cells functioning optimally. Estimate your biological age based on DNA methylation patterns using DunedinPACE.",
